transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Vagra.

Speaker 2: Hi, I'm calling in regards to, 

Speaker 1: you guys, I think you guys put me on auto refill.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: And I need to cancel the auto refill,

Speaker 2: because now I got like more than I need for a while.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Mr. Michael Martin?

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I see that you have a prescription from Dr. Regan

Speaker 2: for 10 tablets every 30 days, Vagra AGV.

Speaker 1: If you don't need it as often, you don't have to get it.

Speaker 2: So I'm going to advise the pharmacy to pause the prescription

Speaker 1: so you can order as needed,

Speaker 2: because you don't have to get it every 30 days as well.

Speaker 1: You can order, you know, when you need it,

Speaker 2: once or twice a year to lock your price in, okay,

Speaker 1: but the monthly is not required.

Speaker 2: So if you have a lot left,

Speaker 1: I'm going to advise the pharmacy to put a pause.

Speaker 2: They pause up to half a year,

Speaker 1: so you don't get it on the monthly anymore, okay?

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Is there anything else you need from me?

Speaker 2: No, that's it.

Speaker 1: We will update the frequency so you can order as needed, okay?

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: And also, I have one more other question,

Speaker 2: because I got it originally when I started this with you guys.

Speaker 1: I was getting the generic one,

Speaker 2: and then I started this AGV one,

Speaker 1: but I know on the pill itself,

Speaker 2: because on the labels that I was getting,

Speaker 1: it wasn't AGV.

Speaker 2: It was still the generic one,

Speaker 1: and I got charged,

Speaker 2: but then you guys re-sent me another one,

Speaker 1: and didn't charge me.

Speaker 2: So I just want to verify that.

Speaker 1: So when I receive it on the label,

Speaker 2: it should say AGV, correct?

Speaker 1: Yes, but more so, more even important,

Speaker 2: because the label is just a label as well sometimes.

Speaker 1: So the pill got to say 100.

Speaker 2: If the pill say 300, some other number,

Speaker 1: that might be a different formula.

Speaker 2: The formula that you want,

Speaker 1: and that's what I see you receive,

Speaker 2: we sent you a replacement,

Speaker 1: say 100 on the pill.

Speaker 2: Okay, good to know.

Speaker 1: Because, yeah, I was receiving the one that said AC340,

Speaker 2: or something like that,

Speaker 1: but I got charged for the AGV,

Speaker 2: but then you guys did re-send me another one.

Speaker 1: Okay, good.

Speaker 2: So as long as it says 100,

Speaker 1: that's the one I want.

Speaker 2: Yeah, that's the code.

Speaker 1: Okay, perfect.

Speaker 2: Alright, yeah, I'll probably re-order in maybe two months,

Speaker 1: but for now I don't need an auto-refill.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Alright, you want me to schedule you for in two months?

Speaker 2: No, I'll just call you guys when I'm getting close.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Alright.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Alright, I appreciate your help.

Speaker 1: You're all set.

Speaker 2: Thank you, sir.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
